  <h1>Glass Tube</h1>
  <h3>Source</h3>
  <text>
    <style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki.<br></br>Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/179043/">花海</style>, <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/Yefancy">KilaBash</style><br></br></style>
  </text>
  <text>Glass tubes, made from glass dust in <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/forming_press" underlined="true">Forming Press</style> or <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/alloy_smelter" underlined="true">Alloy smelter</style>, or from glass liquid in a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/fluid_solidifier" underlined="true">Fluid Solidifier</style> with a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:misc/mold" underlined="true">casting mold (ball)</style>, consume 1 glass material for every 1 glass tube produced. Glass tubes can be made with only LV voltage. <br></br> <br></br> Glass tubes can be used to craft <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:circuits/vacuum_tube" underlined="true">Vacuum Tubes</style>, a primary component of your first circuit.</text>
